title: zenkai_gakuen
body:
全開学園, aka "Full Open Academy".

A very old series by artist [[Duke]] from the mid 90s.  A play on "Zenra Gakuen" (Zenra, of course, being "Stark Naked"), Zenkai Gakuen is a combination of the old "Emperor's New Clothes" fable and, well, high school.

In Zenkai Gakuen, the public school has standardized using a specific, somewhat mundane uniform -- except for the material that it is made out of.  This strange cloth is completely invisible to anyone with an IQ of less than 65536 -- all they see are the collar of the shirt, the tie, and the footwear.

Underwear and casual wear are also provided by the school.

Of course, no one ever admits they can't see the uniform.  That would be tantamount to admitting the aren't very smart.

There is a similar uniform for the elementary school, as well as a boy's uniform -- the boys are mercifully not drawn by Duke, however.

And, just like the original fable, the 8 year old little sister of the main female lead is fully aware that the uniform doesn't actually exist, and that her sister and herself are all walking around completely starkers.

However, A public prosecutor went after the school, only to discover to her dismay that the uniform apparently DOES appear on film.

Some fairly well known artists including AVX have drawn fanart of the series over the years, unfortunately most of it has been lost over several website closures.

h4.Characters

* [[Hazuki Chigusa]] ([[Brown hair]]ed girl)
* [[Hazuki Chisato]] (Chigusa's younger sister)
* [[Copperfield Rumiko]] ([[blonde_hair|Blonde]] girl)
* [[Copperfield Kumiko]] (Rumiko's sister)
* [[Kashiwada Yayoi]] ([[glasses|Meganekko]])

title: funipero
body:
A character from [[Nihei Tsutomu]]'s manga Biomega.

Funipero was created by [[Nyaldee]] as an evolved version of herself, with a means to control the recreated world. Once created, Funipero was to be absorbed by Nyaldee against her will.

She is saved by [[Kanoe Zouichi]] before she is born; together they travel the recreated world while attempting to destroy Nyaldee.

Funipero was born fully sentient, with the ability to walk and talk, and with a supernatural knowledge of the recreated world. She also has many of Nyaldee's powers; she possesses the 'shinensoku', and the power to form constituent manifestations of herself.

title: kanoe_zouichi
body:
The main character from [[Nihei Tsutomu]]'s manga [[Biomega]].

Kanoe Zouichi is a synthetic human created by the fictional Toha Heavy Industries to handle the outbreak of the N5S virus.

Zouichi's mission is to locate and rescue any humans who may have adapted to the virus before [[Nyaldee]] and the Data Recovery Foundation are able to.

Being a synthetic human, Zouichi is capable of superhuman speed, strength, and reflexes, along with increased recovery speed and an indefinite lifespan. He is equiped with a set of pistol coilguns, and a Toha Heavy Industries-designated '4000XLA' motorcycle programmed with his AI partner [[Kanoe Fuyu]], carrying a larger high-powered coilgun.

The PDR (personal defense rifle) is an American-designed compact [[assault rifle]], developed by Magpul Industries in Colorado. It is designed for the same role as the FN [[P90]] and has similar ergonomics, but fires NATO standard 5.56x45mm ammunition and uses the same magazines as the [[M16]] to simplify logistics.

Thus far the PDR has not progressed beyond the prototype stage, and development seems to have been halted.

title: calico_smg
body:
The Calico series are submachine guns (along with civilian semi-automatic pistol and carbine versions) produced by Calico Light Weapons Systems. The M100/M110 series are fire .22 Long Rifle rounds, while the M750/M900/M950/M960 series fire 9x19mm. The 9x19mm versions were later renamed the Calico Liberty I, II, and III. All versions use helical box magazines with a capacity of 50 or 100 rounds, and shell casings are ejected out the bottom similar to the [[P90]].

While civilian semi-automatic sales have been limited and attempts to market the submachine guns to military and law enforcement have been unsuccessful, the Calico series are somewhat popular in science fiction due to their futuristic appearance.

title: qf-2001
body:
A [[mecha]] from the [[Macross]] series. It first appeared in the [[Macross Zero]] OVA from 2002.

The [b]QF-2001 Ghost[/b] is a stealth [[robot]] fighter jet produced by the [[U.N. Spacy]] in 2000. 

As a predecessor to the [[QF-3000E]] used in Space War I (circa 2009) and the Ghost [[X-9]] (circa 2040) the QF-2001 pioneered many of the conventional technologies for modern unmanned stealth fighters. 

The Ghost's large single engine, low mass and upward-canted forward-swept cranked gull wing makes the unmanned fighter very fast and agile. 

The armament of the QF-2001 Ghost drone remains classified however, observers have noted two open ports on the forward ventral hull along side the forward landing gear as well as four closed ports that resemble micro-missile launcher doors on either side of the rear ventral fuselage.

This fighter was frequently used as a fast-pack booster attached to the dorsal fuselage of the [[VF-0]] Phoenix variable fighter.

h4. See also

* [[Ghost Drone]]

Spike wanted to leave the Red Dragon syndicate with Julia, but upon finding out about the affair, Vicious issued Julia an ultimatum: either she was to kill Spike, or Spike and Julia would both face death for her betrayal. title: matin_catorce
body:
Main female character from [[Blind Justice]], twin sister of [[Nox Catorce]].

Matin Catorce, 14 years old (when she first appeared in [[Bemani|Beatmania]] IIDX 14th GOLD Style), right-hander, the "positive" one of the twins, the wielder of The Sword Of Hope - Trisagion. Though she had became the empress of Noigllado for having the ability to wield Trisagion, it's still too young for her to have enough authoritativeness that few ministers and knights swore their oaths of allegiance to her.

She grew up in the palace, the fabulous life made her heart full of love. She did not even know how to hate another one. When she was taught that she had a brother who was abandoned few years ago and he's still alive, she instantly began to pray for him and tried to find him. Though she could feel Nox's hatred from her Ristaccia piece inserted necklace (I believed that Matin had at least three pieces of Ristaccia), she still loved Nox and wanted to save him from hatred. But this does not mean that she is a weak girl. Her heart is adamant enough, and she had a strong sense of justice. She could do anything if it is for her country and her people, even that means to sacrifice herself or to kill her loved one (hence Blind Justice). To safeguard her justice, finally, she put her customized armor (which had one piece of Ristaccia inserted) on, brought the sword of Trisagion up, to fight her loving brother.

Matin means "morning" in French.

See also:

http://www.bemanistyle.com/forum/f5/epic-zektbach-29020/

title: nox_catorce
body:
Main male character from [[Blind Justice]], twin brother of [[Matin Catorce]].

Nox Catorce, 14 years old, left-hander, the "negative" one of the twins, the wielder of The Sword Of Despair - Tyrfing. He was supposed to be a prince,but had been abandoned for having the ability to wield another Ristaccia piece inserted sword - Tyrfing. Matin and Nox are one pair of perfect symmetric, and so does the two swords too. To avoid the possible conflict between the positive one and the negative one, Nox must be abandoned.

But the kind royal sword instructor Adhuc did not want that to happen. He took Nox and the sword of Tyrfing, escaped from the palace, and then Nox became the third child adopted by Adhuc. He grew up in countryside,lead a poor life with Adhuc and the other two children. Adhuc taught him swordmanship. With his talent,Nox became an outstanding swordman. Knowing Nox is a Prince, Adhuc tried his best to economize the use of money to buy some gorgeous suits for Nox, for that, though he lead a tough life, Nox never looked shabby, but always as beautiful as his sister.

Nox had a strong sense of justice. He wanted to fight against the dominators of Holy Kingdom in order to save poor people, thus he joined the Alliance. Later, when he learned about his antecedent, he felt happy for owning an outstanding sister at first (he kept his braid to show his respect to Matin). But finally, with the implacable ressentiment, he had his heart occupied with hatred, and the hatred was amplificated day by day under the influence of the piece of Ristaccia which was inserted in Tyrfing. The Alliance hailed Nox as their leader, but Nox had no interest in taking his country back. He just hated Matin and wanted to kill her.

Nox means "darkness" in Latin, alternatively also refers to Nyx, Greek goddess of the night.

Catorce is "fourteen" in Spanish, possible reference to the fact that these two first appeared in IIDX 14 GOLD.

See also:

http://www.bemanistyle.com/forum/f5/epic-zektbach-29020/

title: curtiss_r3c-0
body:
A fictional [[seaplane]] in the Ghibli movie and manga [[Kurenai no Buta]]. It is a notional version of the Curtiss Aeroplane and Motor Company's R3C pontoon racer that won the "Schneider Cup":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Schneider_Trophy held in Baltimore in 1925.

Flown by Donald Curtis, the R3C-0 is a blue biplane with a yellow rudder and planing surfaces. A white wraparound band with an arrow-through-heart symbol decorates the fuselage, with a stylized rattlesnake at the base of the rudder. It was armed with two .30-caliber machine guns.

title: kagari_(ikaruga)
body:
The secondary protagonist of the shooting game [[Ikaruga]].

A mercenary pilot for the Horai empire, Kagari's [i]butsutekkai[/i] was the first to experience and get shot down by the Ikaruga when it was test-flown. After being rescued by [[shinra_(ikaruga)|Shinra]], she eventually decided to join him in his quest for freedom, and retrieved her personal [i]hitekkai[/i] - the Ginkei - from the wreckage of her butsutekkai to be retrofitted with the same equipment as the Ikaruga.

title: shinra_(ikaruga)
body:
The primary protagonist of the shooting game [[Ikaruga]].

A soldier who fought against the Horai empire to the point of suicide, he was shot down over the ikaruga village, where he was pulled free of the wreckage of his self-made [i]hitekkai[/i] and nursed back to health by the elderly residents. After he had recovered, they brought him to see their secret project - the Ikaruga - and gave it to him to pilot in a final counterassault against the empire for the sake of freedom.
